						<summary>

						<p>Two slabs set up in the Vēṇugōpalasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 143[0], Vibhava, Kārttika śu. 15,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1508 A.D., December, 7 Thursday.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records the gift of some lands to the god Nāganātha for daily worship and offerings by Raṅganātha, son of Jāvunayāka.</p>						

						</summary>
